{"comments":"Easing curves for animation interpolation.\n\nDefines how values change over time between keyframes. The easing\nfunction maps normalized time (0-1) to normalized value (0-1).\n\n## Cubic Bezier\n\nThe foundation is the cubic bezier curve, matching CSS `cubic-bezier()`:\n- Two control points (x1,y1) and (x2,y2)\n- Start point is implicitly (0,0)\n- End point is implicitly (1,1)\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Motion.Easing as Easing\n\n-- Use a preset\nease = Easing.easeInOut\n\n-- Create custom cubic bezier\ncustom = Easing.cubicBezier 0.17 0.67 0.83 0.67\n\n-- Evaluate easing at time t (0-1)\nvalue = Easing.evaluate ease 0.5\n-- Returns the eased value at 50% progress\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[143,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Easing.purs","start":[143,3]},"title":"Linear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Easing"],"CubicBezier"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[144,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Easing.purs","start":[144,3]},"title":"Bezier"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[145,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Easing.purs","start":[145,3]},"title":"Steps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Easing"],"Easing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[147,38],"name":".